content.description: Starting on left most pocket, traverse right and up into crimps and weird side pull. either match on the jug and drop or attempt the top out... haven't quite cleaned it off well just yet but looks pretty easy,
content.protection: 2-3 pads. spotter if you're nervous about the tree.
content.location: left and around the corner from "Magic Fingers" just right of "Maverick Corner"

content.description: Sit start on right hand undercling and left hand slopey edge. Move straight up the rock to pull a strenuous dyno. Top it out or hang and drop after the dyno.

Andy Krick's Vision. Stem into the obvious corner just left of Top Gun. move through jugs to gain a sharp sloper. find the jug shelf past the sloper and hang and drop or get creative with a top out. Classic!
content.location: Just left of Top Gun on Magic Fingers boulder. Obvious Corner

content.description: This line is so bomber.Climbing starts on two low chalked side pulls with a bump out left to a sloping crimp. Top it out between the top of the roof and shelf.
content.protection: At least 4 pads, a spotter if you want, top feels pretty mellow.
content.location: Just before magic fingers there is a slight overhanging face with a clearly chalked up side pull and crimps.

content.description: Sit start on right hand undercling and left hand slopey edge. Work your way up "The Other Side" and then break left before the dyno into powerful crimp moves. Top out by going all the way or by simply standing on the pedestal.
content.protection: A couple of pads, it's not very tall

content.description: Start on the first horizontal crack, finish is the fist sized chicken head straight above. I suggest down climbing to sit on the nice ledge before jumping to your pad. (or find a rockin' top out). I don't leave a lot of chalk behind so sorry to the next guy! My beta: Hands on the first ledge and right foot high step on the tiny crimp. Step up to the nice big ledge, high(ish) feet, then work your way up to the long horizontal crack under the mini roof. Use the big ledge for your feet and find the chicken head looking hold right above your head
content.location: This is somewhere left of the main Warrior Wall before getting to the Gypsum section. When finding the wall, the is a rounded corner that is a little more reddish, has lots of lichen and is generally wet and then the climb is to the left of that.

content.description: Sit start on double undercling and surf out to the arête to a hang and drop jug.
content.location: Starts around the corner on the right from the Crack Head Super Powers Project.

content.description: Fantastic line if it’s been dry a few days.Swim jugs as far as you can into a big move to a sloper. move up and out through the iron banded slabby Arête.If you top if out go straight back into the woods and you’ll find the trail again. Or you can go left and find the down climb for “Magic Toes”
content.protection: A few pads. Maybe a spotter but the falls are actually pretty chill.
content.location: Just before the battle roof right before the entrance to that deep bear cave. Start on the lowest mega jug.

content.description: On the left end of the roof. Start on some good edges at chest height. Work left out the roof on some perfectly sculpted pinches and underclings on pockets to a move to a big jug horn at the lip. Match the jug above and drop (There may eventually be a topout, but the FA was done as a hang-and-drop).Beta Video of FA
content.location: On the same roof as Battle Tactics, about 30ft to the left. This is the third roof (west) you come to when walking in from the approach trail.

content.description: Start in a jug slot under a little mini roof. Find holds to get out to a rail and follow it to finish in a little hueco. Hang and drop.
content.protection: Pads. The landing is a little uneven.
content.location: On the right side of the second big roof that you get to along the Warrior Wall.GPS Location: 36.095085, -84.821005

content.description: This is a long section of low cliff line on the East Side. There are several large roofs tall faces housing a number of boulder problems and even some trad routes. Approach via the orange flagged trail and descend the cliff band by a low angle slick rock. You will immediately see a huge roof with some bed springs and other junk below it. Continue climbers left to the next big roof which houses Camelot and Battle Tactics. The cliff line continues going climbers left with a few more roofs and faces until it starts petering out after Crack House.
